Very early in the game, you're prompted to leave a review. That's where I'm at now, and I think that's as far as I'll go. There's definitely potential, but the annoyances win out for me. The "puzzles" are often unintuitive, best solved via guesswork (i.e., randomly tapping) and using hints; the hidden objects are sometimes just too dark to see; the hints are often useless, since they don't account for items you've already found; and up close, the graphics are pixelated and unclear.

I enjoy hidden object games quite a bit, and I recently subscribed to Google Play Pass (which includes this). So I decided to give this game a try! And I have to say, it's pretty good! Many of the puzzles are difficult enough to give a slight challenge, but they never become frustrating. In addition, I thought there was a good variety to the puzzles and hidden object sequences. I even saw a few completely new puzzles. Overall, I enjoyed this game, and I'd recommend it to fans of the genre!

The main story is decent, but the additional story is the most annoying puzzle ever. You have multiple tools that could do a job but you're only allowed to use one specific one, active areas are not well marked and you're constantly having to back track for over little tool or hint.
